THOUGHT: The crash occurs due to DT->getNode(BB) returning null in optimizeGatherSequence when building the CSE worklist, leading to an assertion. A conservative fix is to skip basic blocks that are not present in the dominator tree. I will modify the loop that populates CSEWorkList to continue when DT->getNode(BB) is null, preventing the subsequent assert and dominance misuse. Then I will submit the patch to rebuild and validate.

```bash
sed -i 's/for (BasicBlock \*BB : CSEBlocks)
    if (DomTreeNode \*N = DT->getNode(BB)) {
      assert(DT->isReachableFromEntry(N));
      CSEWorkList.push_back(N);
    }/for (BasicBlock *BB : CSEBlocks) {
    if (DomTreeNode *N = DT->getNode(BB)) {
      assert(DT->isReachableFromEntry(N));
      CSEWorkList.push_back(N);
    } else {
      /* Skip blocks not present in the dominator tree to avoid dominance issues. */
      continue;
    }
  }/' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && submit-patch
```

